    <item>
      <title>Putting the Git Branch Name on the Command Prompt</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/git-branch-name-on-command-prompt/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 21 May 2025 17:03:20 -0700</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/git-branch-name-on-command-prompt/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I originally posted this in Octopress on Dec 11th 2014.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sometimes it’s handy to always see which branch of the repository we’re working in. We can display this as part of the terminal command prompt by adding a few things to our local &lt;code&gt;~/.bash_profile&lt;/code&gt; file.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;# Filename: ~/.bash_profile&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; parse_git_branch &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;  git branch 2&amp;gt; /dev/null &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; sed -e &lt;span class=&#34;s1&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;/^[^*]/d&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; -e &lt;span class=&#34;s1&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;s/* \(.*\)/ (\1)/&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;4&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;# This will display the current folder&amp;#39;s full path.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;6&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;# If you want only the folder name, replace \w with \W&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;7&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;export&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nv&#34;&gt;PS1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;\[\e]0;\u@\h: \w\a\]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;si&#34;&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nv&#34;&gt;debian_chroot&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:+(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nv&#34;&gt;$debian_chroot&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;si&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;\u@\h:\w\[\033[36m\]\$(parse_git_branch)\[\033[0m\]\$ &amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;
